a &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; tone is a short-term auditory illusion which resembles &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( ringing of the ears ) . it was discovered in 1964 by eberhard &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; at bell labs . the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; tone can be described as follows : while listening to &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; noise ( " white noise " ) with a &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; gap , if it is switched off a faint tone lasting for several seconds can be heard . in the silence , most listeners hear a tone corresponding to the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; gap . the pitch strength corresponds to the pitch strength of a pure tone of same pitch and sensation level .